            "padding-block-end": 0,
            "padding-inline-start": 0,
            "padding-inline-end": 0
          },
          "blocks": {}
        },
        "text_ahKGbw": {
          "type": "text",
          "name": "t:names.text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>This skin type does best on a short, gentle routine.<br/><br/>Cleanse gently rather than harshly, with lukewarm water, since stripping the skin tends to provoke both more oil and more reaction. Keep the routine simple, and resist piling on strong actives, since reactive skin has less tolerance for them. Introduce new things one at a time, with a patch test, so that if something doesn't suit you, you know exactly what it was. And give any change a few weeks. With this skin type, less really is more.<br/><br/>You'll have noticed we never use synthetic fragrance, which is one of the more common triggers for skin like this. There's a single essential oil in the range, <a href=\"/blogs/ingredients/vetiver-vetiveria-zizanioides-root-oil\" title=\"Vetiveria Zizanoides (Vetiver) Root Oil\">vetiver</a>, at a low level and chosen on purpose, and it appears on every label so you can see exactly how much is there.<br/></p>",
            "width": "fit-content",
            "max_width": "normal",
            "alignment": "left",
            "type_preset": "rte",
            "font": "var(--font-body--family)",
            "font_size": "1rem",
            "line_height": "normal",
            "letter_spacing": "normal",
            "case": "none",
            "wrap": "pretty",
            "text_color": "",
            "background": false,
            "background_color": "#00000026",
            "corner_radius": 0,
            "padding-block-start": 0,
            "padding-block-end": 0,
            "padding-inline-start": 0,
            "padding-inline-end": 0
          },
          "blocks": {}
        },
        "text_iiUCEX": {
          "type": "text",
          "name": "t:names.heading",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Your skin can settle over time</p>",
            "width": "fit-content",
            "max_width": "normal",
            "alignment": "left",
            "type_preset": "h3",
            "font": "var(--font-body--family)",
            "font_size": "1rem",
            "line_height": "normal",
            "letter_spacing": "normal",
            "case": "none",
            "wrap": "pretty",
            "text_color": "",
            "background": false,
            "background_color": "#00000026",
            "corner_radius": 0,
            "padding-block-start": 0,
            "padding-block-end": 0,
            "padding-inline-start": 0,
            "padding-inline-end": 0
          },
          "blocks": {}
        },
        "text_hVYV6M": {
          "type": "text",
          "name": "t:names.text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Oily Sensitive isn't a fixed label. Cared for gently and simply, the reactivity often calms over time, and for some people the skin gradually settles toward the steadier Oily type, where there's less to tiptoe around. It's gradual, it comes from a kind, consistent, uncomplicated routine rather than any single product working magic, and it's a good reason to treat where your skin is today as a starting point. If it changes, the skin type finder is always there to place yourself again.</p>",
            "width": "fit-content",
            "max_width": "normal",
            "alignment": "left",
            "type_preset": "rte",
            "font": "var(--font-body--family)",
            "font_size": "1rem",
